00:00:20.230 --> 00:00:21.540
is diabetic retinopathy?

00:00:21.540 --> 00:00:23.290
DR. JORGE CUADROS: So
diabetic retinopathy

00:00:23.290 --> 00:00:25.750
is the main cause of blindness
among working-age adults

00:00:25.750 --> 00:00:26.830
in the world.

00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:31.960
And the sad thing is
that it's 90% preventable

00:00:31.960 --> 00:00:36.650
if patients would get regular
eye exams and timely treatment.

00:00:36.650 --> 00:00:38.980
The problem is that people
don't get regular eye exams,

00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:44.710
and so we've been going out and
getting images of the retina

00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:48.250
in order to get a
diagnosis to see who is

00:00:48.250 --> 00:00:49.567
at risk for vision impairment.

00:00:49.567 --> 00:00:51.400
TIMOTHY JORDAN: And how
do you apply machine

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:52.930
learning to the problem?

00:00:52.930 --> 00:00:58.300
DR. JORGE CUADROS: So right now
an ophthalmologist or an eye

00:00:58.300 --> 00:01:00.850
doctor optometrist has
to look at the image

00:01:00.850 --> 00:01:03.280
and determine what the
level of retinal disease

00:01:03.280 --> 00:01:06.880
is before a patient
can be referred,

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:09.320
if they need referral
for treatment.

00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:14.890
So with AI you can get an
immediate grading of what's

00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:16.570
going on in the retina.

00:01:16.570 --> 00:01:19.570
So you don't have to wait
sometimes an hour or two hours

00:01:19.570 --> 00:01:23.290
or two or three days or even
weeks to get a response.

00:01:23.290 --> 00:01:26.310
You can act immediately
for people that need care.

00:01:26.310 --> 00:01:29.410
TIMOTHY JORDAN: And I imagine
this is a scalable thing

00:01:29.410 --> 00:01:31.720
as well for areas
that don't have access

00:01:31.720 --> 00:01:33.310
to the same medical help.

00:01:33.310 --> 00:01:34.351
DR. JORGE CUADROS: Right.

